title: We make language learning easier and more fun
subtitle: Language learning is hard. We want to change this, by connecting native speakers together using video calls.

items.title: Native speakers
items.description: The best way to practice another language is by speaking with natives. Lingoers connects you with native speakers of the language you're practicing.

items.title: Video calling
items.description: Video is the closest you can get to face-to-face. With Lingoers, you can video call native speakers and have real-time conversations from your phone.

items.title: Conversations
items.description: We get it! Sometimes conversations dry up. Lingoers shows you things you can say (prompts) while you're in a call, so you always have things to talk about.

items.title: Confidence
items.description: It's common to feel shy when speaking with native speakers. Lingoers improves your confidence by matching people based on their level.

testimonials.name: John Billington
testimonials.comment: I find it really difficult to practice other languages - I use Memrise and Duolingo but can never really get past saying basic phrases! I feel like this could bridge the gap and help me get fluent in Spanish!

testimonials.name: Katie Francis
testimonials.comment: I'm currently using Duolingo to practice Italian but when I'm trying to speak with a native speaker, I almost can't understand anything! I'm excited to be a part of this journey with Lingoers as I can't wait to be able to speak with native Italians!

faqs.question: What is Lingoers?
faqs.answer: It's a mobile app; a social network that connects natives speakers with each other, using live video.

faqs.question: Can I download it?
faqs.answer: Yes, you will be able to download the app from the app store (Android and iOS). However, we're working on it currently so it's not available yet - but feel free to enter your email to join our waiting list above to be the first to hear about it!

faqs.question: Does it cost?
faqs.answer: It will be free to download and use. Just like many other language apps - it will use a 'freemium' plan, where anyone can download and use it.

faqs.question: What happens after I enter my email?
faqs.answer: If you enter your email where it says "Register your interest", it simply keeps you in the loop as to what's happening with the app and when it will be available.

faqs.question: What's the story behind it?
faqs.answer: The app is being created by James Hutchinson. He did an Erasmus exchange year in Castellon (Spain). When he returned to the UK, he missed speaking Spanish. This is where Lingoers came about - which uses live video calling to help practice with native speakers, in a natural, conversational way.

items.title: "Why speed matters in business: lessons from Olympic athletes"
items.description:
Speed is crucial in the product development process, just like in sports where even fractions of a second can make all the difference. In the 2021 Olympic Games in Tokyo, Canadian sprinter Andre De Grasse won a bronze medal in the 100-meter dash with just a 0.06 second difference from the gold medalist. This highlights how small delays or mistakes can significantly impact your chances of success.

In the same way, in business, even minor delays or setbacks can result in the loss of competitive advantage or customers. Therefore, it's essential to use tools and technologies that help increase your speed and efficiency.

By utilizing tools that save time and allow you to focus on other important aspects, you can maximize your productivity and effectiveness. This is especially crucial when it comes to website development. The faster your website is designed and launched, the quicker you can begin promoting yourself, attracting customers, and generating revenue.

items.title: "Simplicity in Action: Why Simple Things are Popular?"
items.description:
We often tend to think that the more complex something is, the better it works or looks. However, in reality, simple things can be much more effective, convenient, and reliable than complex ones. Below are a few examples that demonstrate why simple things are always better than complex ones.

 Bottle opener. This is a really simple thing that we use every day and that doesn't require any special skills to use. 

Pen. A pen is another simple item that we use every day and that doesn't require charging or maintenance. 

Glass. A glass is another very simple thing that we use every day and that can be used for different drinks. 

The conclusion that can be drawn from this is that the simpler and more understandable an item is, the more intuitively it is used, and the more popular it becomes. Simple things that don't require complex skills are suitable for a wide range of people and can be used in different situations, making them indispensable in our everyday life.

items.title: To be in the spotlight. Why companies need to be media-savvy?
items.description:
In today's world, competition among companies is increasing, making it essential to stand out and attract customers. Being media-savvy is crucial for companies, which means using various media to promote their brand and products. 

Media exposure can start with simply sharing company successes and progress, gathering feedback, and openly communicating with people. This helps companies attract attention and learn about their customers' opinions, which can improve products and satisfy customer needs. 

When a company becomes media-savvy, it gains visibility among competitors, potentially leading to increased sales, stronger branding, and customer loyalty. Media exposure can also attract investors and investments. 

For example, Tesla became media-savvy through its innovative technology and unique products, actively using social media and other media to promote its brand and products, leading to worldwide recognition and attracting many customers and investors. 

Our product is an ideal tool for companies that want to be media-savvy, allowing easy sharing of information among like-minded individuals focused on results, providing an excellent way to receive feedback and share progress with a broad audience. But this is not the only advantage of our product. We have also focused on creating an intuitive and user-friendly interface, enabling our users to maximize the product's efficiency. Such an approach disciplines and motivates users, critical for achieving success in any field.

faqs.question: What is augmented reality (AR) and how is it related to social networks?
faqs.answer:
Augmented reality (AR) is a technology that allows digital content to be overlaid onto the real world. This content can be viewed through a smartphone or other device, creating a seamless blend of the digital and physical worlds.

AR is becoming increasingly popular in social networks as it allows users to create immersive and interactive experiences that can be shared with their friends and followers. For example, AR filters and lenses on platforms like Snapchat and Instagram allow users to add fun and engaging effects to their photos and videos, while Facebook's Spark AR Studio lets users create their own AR experiences.

faqs.question: How can social networks use AR to benefit businesses?
faqs.answer:
Social networks are a powerful marketing tool for businesses, and AR can take that to the next level. By incorporating AR into their social media campaigns, businesses can create unique and engaging experiences for their customers, increase brand awareness, and drive sales.

For example, a fashion retailer could use AR to allow customers to virtually try on clothes, while a home decor store could use AR to let customers see how furniture would look in their homes. These types of experiences can be shared on social media, increasing the reach and impact of the campaign.

faqs.question: How does augmented reality (AR) differ from virtual reality (VR)?
faqs.answer: While both AR and VR are immersive technologies, there is a key difference between the two. AR overlays digital content onto the real world, while VR creates a completely immersive digital environment. AR allows users to interact with both the real and digital world, while VR is a fully digital experience.

faqs.question: What is the future of augmented reality?
faqs.answer: The future of augmented reality is exciting and rapidly evolving. As technology continues to advance, we can expect to see more widespread adoption of AR in various industries and applications. AR is likely to become more immersive, interactive, and seamlessly integrated into our daily lives.

faqs.question: I already use Trello, Notion, Airtable, etc... how is this different?
faqs.answer:
Those are great! The difference between these tools and Ellie is that Ellie was specifically built as a day planner / brain dump. You can "hack" together a system like this with Notion or Airtable, but the UI won't be the same.
The biggest thing that is hard to replicate is the "infinite" Kanban view where you can scroll between dates infinitely. Ellie also has a great timebox view that you can't replicate with other apps.

There are also some features like  Google & Apple calendar integration, Siri shortcut support, advanced filtering, focus mode, task roll-over, recurring tasks and other little things that you won't find in most systems. As time goes on, I'll be adding more features such as calendar integrations and basic anlaytics.

faqs.question: Who would be a good fit for Ellie?
faqs.answer:
If you want a simple app, Ellie is a good fit.

If like this "Braindump + Daily Kanban" planning system, Ellie is a good fit.

If you want a beautiful native iOS app, Ellie is a good fit.

faqs.question: As a one person operation, how can I trust that you will be around in a year or two?

The costs of the app are very low and I am using profits from my other apps (example: Mogul) to fund things for now.

I have no plans to raise money or make my apps a big thing so you don't have to worry about things shutting down because they aren't growing fast enough/generating enough returns for investors.

My other app Mogul has been around for almost 5 years and is very much alive. I plan on keeping this app up and running indefinitely.

We do have an iOS app!
